details.detail:
&lt;p&gt;1. Throw all stems and about half of the mushrooms cut up, carrots, celery and onions into broth, add water until the mushrooms and veggies are just covered. Bring to a boil then simmer. Add herbs. Simmer for 2 hours or until the veggies go to mush.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;2. Puree the wild mushrooms with stick blender. Add some more stock if needed, puree once more.&amp;nbsp;&lt;br /&gt;
&lt;br /&gt;
3. Sautee the remaining mushrooms in (lots of) butter, then toss them in the soup and add the cream. Thicken a bit with a few shakes of arrowroot and salt/pepper to taste.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;4. Simmer for another hour and serve with a swirl of truffle oil and some cracked black pepper.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/p&gt;
